# üîå Connectors (First-Class)

Connectors are a first-class provider category that bring external data into a Project.

Every connector implements `BaseSourceConnector` and supports:

* Authentication / credential handling
* Listing available items
* Fetching content + metadata
* Incremental sync (change detection)
* Health / status reporting

Connectors feed the data lifecycle through Storage; they never bypass it or write directly to the Vector DB.

Concrete connectors (File Upload, SQL, API, Website, SharePoint, Google Drive, S3) are interchangeable implementations behind this interface.

