# üè≠ Production & Enterprise Standards

## API Versioning

All public routes are versioned under `/api/v1/...`. Breaking changes require a new version, never a silent change to an existing one.

---

## API reference documentation (`docs/api/`)

Maintain a **module-grouped API collection** under `docs/api/` ‚Äî concise reference
for Postman import, not tutorials.

* `docs/api/README.md` ‚Äî base URL, response envelope, module index
* One file per module: `docs/api/projects.md`, `docs/api/knowledge.md`, ‚Ä¶
* Per endpoint: method, path, one-line purpose, sample request/response JSON
* Update when routes ship or change; OpenAPI (`/docs`) remains the live contract

---

## Database Migrations

All schema changes go through Alembic migrations. Never auto-create or mutate tables at runtime in production.

---

## Standard Error Model

Errors return a consistent envelope: `code`, `message`, `trace_id`, and optional `details`. No raw stack traces leak to clients.

---

## Idempotency

Ingestion and job submission must be idempotent via idempotency keys or content hashes, so retries never cause duplicate processing.

---

## Health & Readiness

Expose:

* `/health` ‚Äî liveness
* `/ready` ‚Äî dependency checks (PostgreSQL, Redis, Vector DB, providers)

---

## Data Deletion

Deleting a Project or Document cascades across PostgreSQL, the Vector Store, and Object Storage to support right-to-be-forgotten.

---

## Configuration Precedence

Resolution order:

```
defaults ‚Üí environment ‚Üí database ‚Üí per-Project overrides
```

---

## Testing

* Unit-test services with faked providers and repositories.
* Contract-test each provider against its abstract interface.
* Integration-test full pipelines end-to-end.

---

## Containerization

Ship as Docker images. Provide a docker-compose stack for the full self-hosted deployment (API, worker, PostgreSQL, Qdrant, Redis, object storage).

